`=` is equivalent to `<h1>`

[Section Titles (Headings)](http://asciidoctor.org/docs/asciidoc-syntax-quick-reference/#section-titles)

```
/** = the example */
private String example;
```

is equivalent to:

```
/** <h1> the example */
private String example;
```

What I meant:

`=` is not used to flag 'this is asciidoc' rather than normal javadoc
